ME1200VlanEgressTagging.name: ME1200VlanEgressTagging
ME1200VlanEgressTagging.description: An integer that indicates how egress tagging occurs.

ME1200VlanIngressAcceptance.name: ME1200VlanIngressAcceptance
ME1200VlanIngressAcceptance.description: An integer that indicates the type of frames that are not discarded on ingress w.r.t. VLAN tagging.

ME1200VlanPortMode.name: ME1200VlanPortMode
ME1200VlanPortMode.description: Determines the underlying port mode. Access ports are only members of one VLAN, the AccessVlan. Trunk ports are by default members of all VLANs, which can be limited with TrunkVlans. Hybrid ports allow for changing all port VLAN parameters. As trunk ports, hybrid ports are by default members of all VLANs, which can be limited with HybridVlans.

ME1200VlanPortType.name: ME1200VlanPortType
ME1200VlanPortType.description: An integer that indicates if a port is VLAN aware, and if so, to which EtherType it is sensitive.

ME1200VlanUserType.name: ME1200VlanUserType
ME1200VlanUserType.description: An integer that indicates the VLAN user type. A value of 'combined' indicates the VLAN settings as programmed to hardware. A value of 'admin' indicates the VLAN settings as programmed by the administrative user, and any other value indicates a software module that changes VLAN settings 'behind the scenes'.

me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMin.name: me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMin
me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMin.description: The minimum VLAN ID that can be configured on the device.

me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMax.name: me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMax
me1200VlanCapabilitiesVlanIdMax.description: The maximum VLAN ID that can be configured on the device.

me1200VlanCapabilitiesFidCnt.name: me1200VlanCapabilitiesFidCnt
me1200VlanCapabilitiesFidCnt.description: The number of Shared VLAN Learning (SVL) Filter IDs (FIDs) supported by this device. 0 if SVL is not supported.

me1200VlanConfigInterfacesSvlTable.name: me1200VlanConfigInterfacesSvlTable
me1200VlanConfigInterfacesSvlTable.description: Shared VLAN Learning (SVL) allows for having one or more VLAN IDs map to the same Filter ID (FID). For a given set of VLANs, if an individual MAC address is learned in one VLAN, that learned information is used in forwarding decisions taken for that address relative to all other VLANs in the given set. fidCnt, which can be found in the capabilities section, indicates the number of FIDs available on this platform. The feature is not available if this number is 0.
